===Transitive verb===
'''verb''' ([[verbs]], [[verbed]], [[verbing]])

#{{colloquial}} to use any word that is not a verb (especially a noun) as if it were a verb.

====Quotations====
* '''1986''': Any noun can be ''verbed'' — Dan Davis, describing the creation of bad technical writing.
